When instructing students individually and in groups, I would use a variety of teaching methods such as lectures to present new information, discussions to encourage critical thinking and collaboration, and demonstrations to show hands-on examples of concepts. I would also use visual aids, such as pictures and diagrams, to help students understand complex ideas. Additionally, I would provide opportunities for students to ask questions and share their thoughts, ensuring that each student has a chance to participate and engage with the material.
